This bug can't be reproduced on Ant 1.7.0 on Windows; I get exactly the same error for both the non-existent folder "/notexist" and "\notexist".

I don't have access to a Mac; what does the following program print on your system? (it should be two "false" lines).

public class SlashFileTest {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.err.println(new java.io.File("\\notexist").exists());
        System.err.println(new java.io.File("/notexist").exists());
    }
}
